<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/36093816-greg"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/36093816-greg">Greg</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">We may never know... ;-)<br/><br/>However, it is line with Marlowe&apos;s quirky ethics. Several times throughout the book he refuses to accept payment over and beyo<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">We may never know... ;-)<br /><br />However, it is line with Marlowe's quirky ethics. Several times throughout the book he refuses to accept payment over and beyond what he thinks he is owed. Therefore, we can conjecture that he thought the pigskin suitcase was far too valuable to accept, even as a gift.<br /><br />Maybe.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
